DORSUM. With two pairs of sigillae, yellowish brown, proximally with a white band followed by irregular black markings posteriorly (
Fig. 1C
). Venter of opisthosoma yellowish brown, with black markings. Dorsum of prosoma yellowish brown, with longitudinal dark brown band. Cervical groove distinct, radial furrows indistinct (
Fig. 1C
).

MEASUREMENTS. Total length 5.50. Prosoma 2.03 long, 1.59 wide; opisthosoma 3.73 long, 3.09 wide (
Fig. 1D
). Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.11, ALE 0.15, PME 0.15, PLE 0.14; AME–AME 0.10, AME–ALE 0.11, PME–PME 0.09, PME–PLE 0.13, ALE–PLE 0.04. MOA 0.40 long, front width 0.34, back width 0.40. Clypeus 0.07 high.
